  "prompt": "Can dogs digest bones?",
  "response": "Dogs can digest bones, but there are certain types and ways to offer bones that are safer than others. Raw bones, especially those from non-weight-bearing parts of animals such as chicken wings, necks, and non-weight-bearing bones from larger animals like beef or lamb, are generally safer for dogs to gnaw on and digest. Cooking bones can make them brittle and more prone to splintering, which can pose serious risks including choking, internal injuries, or obstructions.\n\nIt's important to supervise your dog while they chew on bones and choose appropriately sized bones to minimize the risk of choking. Additionally, certain health conditions and individual dietary needs might affect whether bones are a suitable option for your dog, so consulting a veterinarian for personalized advice is always recommended.",
